picked tentative name parsec or parse c 04/11/2026

Parse master file table written in C

Initial release and will update shortly such as converting to system time which currently uses UTC (which is -7:00 where 
I am). This is because the MFT uses UTC. The filesize of the parser is 170kb and it is fairly fast. I chose C as the job
suites it perfectly suited for the task.

usage:

optional drive (default C:)
./parser.exe
or
./parser.exe S:
./parser.exe C: --cutoff "2026-03-19 10:13:18"

will output in format:
recordnumber frn parent_frn mtime ctime fileattrib isdir|name|path


optional argument (one max)

search for new files by time (UTC)
--cutoff "2026-03-19 10:13:18" or 2026-03-19T10:13:18

list mft record
--target <recordno>

same as with default usage but better format for parsing for Qt gui will output in format:
recordnumber|frn|parent_frn|mtime|ctime|fileattrib|isdir|name|path
--parse

